      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AUSSIE NATION (3) fourth-up for this and looks to find his race from the low draw with the claim. Returned a solid set of closing splits with a tidy second over 2000m at Hawkesbury. Can race a touch closer and get the job done. GRANDINI (4) consistent Scone-trained mare who deserves her chance in provincial company. Caught the eye two-back at Scone, then jumped in trip with a fast finishing nose victory as fav over 1750m at Muswellbrook. Will appreciate the good drop in weight and has genuine claims. MONTY BE QUICK (1) gets a better set-up for this and not without solid top-three prospects. Sat on the good tempo with a plugging fourth over 2000m at Hawkesbury. No surprise to see him return to winning form. NGUNNAWAL (2) appreciated the drop in grade with a well-deserved on-pace victory over 1600m at Taree. Should get the trip fifth-up and stays in the mix.",
